## About The Project

![Product Screenshot](data:image/jpeg;base64,)


Here's why this project is for beginners:

- It involves using Google Mail and a python-based modules which is a new concept to beginners.
- It opens the developer's/learner's perspective about operands/operators.
- You should implement DRY principles to the rest of your life.


Create a `index.py` file to get started and try to replicate it.

### Installation

_Below is an example of how you can instruct your audience on installing and setting up your app. This template doesn't rely on any external dependencies or services._

1. Get a free App Key at [Google App Passwords](https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords)
2. Clone the repo
   ```sh
   git clone https://github.com/LimitedIsListed/Python-Login.git
   ```
3. Enter your APP Key in `gui.py`
   ```py
   server.login(from_email, 'APP_KEY_HERE')
   ```
4. Enter your gmail in `gui.py`
 ```py
 from_email = ''
```
